All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BackToLoginListener
    This class provides the functionality of the "Back To Login" button displayed to the user.
    Client
    Client class for playing the Tool Shop inventory system.
    CloseListener
    This class sends the necessary information to the server to inform it that a client has closed(disconnected) their user interface and quit the application.
    DecreaseItemListener
    This class provides the functionality for a user to decrease an items quantity that currently exists in their inventory.
    GUIController
    This class provides the inherited methods implemented from ActionListener to all of its sub classes, as well as providing access to the MainMenu object a Client is interacting with and the Client themselves.
    LoginListener
    This class provides the necessary methods for user login functionality.
    MainMenu
    This class contains the member variables necessary to construct a user interface representing a retail store's inventory system.
    RemoveItemListener
    This class provides the necessary methods to allow a user to remove a specified item from the inventory.
    SearchBar
    This class sets the size and appearance of a search bar.
    SearchBarListener
    This class contains the necessary methods to allow a user to search for any item in the inventory by the item's ID or name by entering it into a text field.
    ViewConstants
    This interface provides dimensions,fonts and other constants that are used to organize,separate and enhance components within a JFrame object.
    ViewInventoryListener
    This class provides the necessary methods to update the display of the inventory to the user from the click of a button.
